description.narrative: 1. Ensure access to ravidasvir for people still waiting for a cure while expanding DNDi's partnerships to bolster affordable and sustainable supply of all direct-acting antivirals. 2. Foster the political will and financing needed for widescale roll-out of life-saving testing and treatment.

Together with its partners, DNDi developed ravidasvir for use as part of an effective, simple-to-use, affordable treatment for HCV that can increase access and minimize financial burden on patients and health systems. DNDi has also joined with government and civil society groups in Malaysia, industry partners, and FIND, the global alliance for diagnostics, to pioneer the ‘test-and-treat’ strategies needed to scale up access to diagnosis and treatment and achieve ambitions to eliminate the disease worldwide.
